# ============================================================================
# .dockerignore — paperless-ui-chat
# ============================================================================
#
# Files and directories listed here are excluded from the Docker build context.
# This reduces the size of the context sent to the Docker daemon, improves
# build cache efficiency, and prevents sensitive files from entering the image.
#
# ============================================================================

# ── Version control ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Git metadata is never needed inside a container image.
.git
.github
.gitignore

# ── IDE & tooling ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Editor configurations, workspace settings, and AI coding tools.
.vscode
.codebase-wiki
.pi
.pi-lens

# ── Dependencies & build artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────────
# These are re-created inside the container during the build process.
# Excluding them prevents version mismatches between host and container.
node_modules
.pnpm-store
.nuxt
.output
.data

# ── Environment files ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Never ship .env files into the image — they contain secrets.
# Keep .env.example as a template (negation pattern).
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ── Docker files ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Prevent Docker from recursively including its own configuration files
# in the build context (harmless but adds unnecessary size).
Dockerfile*
docker-compose*.yml

# ── Documentation ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# README, license, and agent instructions are not needed at runtime.
README.md
AGENTS.md
LICENSE

# ── OS files ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# macOS and Windows thumbnail caches / system files.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── Build outputs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Test coverage reports and dist outputs.
coverage
dist

# ── Logs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Debug and error log files from various package managers.
*.log
npm-debug.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
